1 bunch baby broccoli
1 packet couscous
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 tomato
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Caramelised Onion Chutney
1 bunch dill
olive oil
1 packet falafel bites
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Boil the kettle
• Break falafel into halves. Trim babybroccoli
• Heat a drizzle of olive oil in frying pan over high heat
• Cook falafel and baby broccoli with a generous splash of water, tossing, until golden and tender, 4-6 mins
• Transfer baby broccoli to a plate
• Add spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil to pan. Stir until fragrant, 1 min

• Meanwhile, combine couscous, vegetable stock and boiling water (3/4 cup for 2P / 1 1/2 cups for 4P) in a bowl
• Cover and set aside for 5 mins
• Roughly chop tomato and almonds
• In a bowl, combine herb mayo and yoghurt

• Add tomato and spinach to couscous
• Plate up couscous, falafel and babybroccoli
• Serve drizzled with yoghurt dressing
• Top with onion chutney, almonds and torn dill